The paper proposes a neural encoder-aligner-decoder model for selective generation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the model uses LSTM-based recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions using a k-nearest neighbor beam filter, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
